#: artemis/reporting/modules/cors_scanner/template_cors_misconfiguration.jinja2:2
msgid "The following addresses have a CORS misconfiguration that allows arbitrary external websites to read authenticated responses:"
msgstr ""

#: artemis/reporting/modules/cors_scanner/template_cors_misconfiguration.jinja2:7
msgid "reflected origins:"
msgstr ""

#: artemis/reporting/modules/cors_scanner/template_cors_misconfiguration.jinja2:13
msgid ""
"A CORS (Cross-Origin Resource Sharing) misconfiguration was detected. The server reflects "
"arbitrary Origin headers in its Access-Control-Allow-Origin response while also setting "
"Access-Control-Allow-Credentials: true. This means any website can make authenticated "
"cross-origin requests and read the responses, potentially stealing sensitive user data."
msgstr ""

#: artemis/reporting/modules/cors_scanner/template_cors_misconfiguration.jinja2:20
msgid ""
"We recommend configuring CORS to only allow specific trusted origins. Do not reflect "
"arbitrary Origin headers. If cross-origin credentials are not needed, remove the "
"Access-Control-Allow-Credentials header."
msgstr ""
